DisplayName.value: 7 Series Integrated Block for PCI Express

Description.value: The Xilinx 7 Series Integrated Block for PCI Express (1-lane, 2-lane, 4-lane, and 8-lane) uses the 7-Series Integrated Hard IP Block for PCI Express in conjunction with flexible 7-Series architectural features to implement a PCI Express Base Specification v2.1 compliant PCI Express Endpoint or Root Port. Unique features of the LogiCORE Block for PCI Express are the high performance AXI Interface, optimal buffering for high bandwidth applications, and BAR checking and filtering.

The AXI4-Stream Interconnect IP provides the infrastructure to connect multiple AXI4-Stream masters and slaves. The configurable interconnect features a 16x16 switch, data FIFOs, register slices, data width converters and clock rate converters.
The AXI Virtual FIFO Controller is a parameterizable number of multi channel FIFO.

The Xilinx Ten Gigabit Ethernet PCS/PMA (10GBASE-R) core is designed to the IEEE specification 802.3 2008. An example design and development scripts are provided to accelerate your design cycle. For 10GBASE-KR interest, please contact your local Xilinx sales representative.

The 10 Gigabit Ethernet Media Access Controller (XGMAC) LogiCORE provides a 32-bit Ten Gigabit Media Independent Interface (XGMII) to provide up to 10 gigabits per second (Gbps) total bandwidth. Operating with an internal clock speed of 156.25MHz, the core supports LAN/WAN mode operation and is designed to the IEEE 802.3-2008 standard specification. In addition, it provides support for VLAN and JUMBO frames . It also provides optional network management features including statistics gathering and flow control. The core can be configured and monitored through a AXI Streaming interface. In addition, the core is designed to seamlessly connect to the XAUI LogiCORE, RXAUI LogiCore and the 10-Gigabit Ethernet PCS/PMA via the XGMII interface.
